      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot Garden, ¶ 12/10/71 ¶  ¶ In first instance dear Mr Guilfoyle, let me express my grateful appreciation of the felicitation, which you bestow on my elevation to a new rank. ¶ Letter not fou...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.10.12a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Michael<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Guilfoyle</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS 439c, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M does not indicate whether his letter is addressed to Michael Guilfoyle or his son William Guilfoyle, but the subject-matter and tone suggest the father.</p>
               </note>Melbourne bot Garden,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">12/10/71</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In first instance dear Mr Guilfoyle, let me express my grateful appreciation of the felicitation, which you bestow on my elevation to a new rank.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Your kindness is all the more touching to me, as I experienced already so much generosity from you and have on your consideration so little claim.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My baronial dignity, which is hereditary, came from Germany, and does not entitle me to the British Predicates, with which you so flattering honor me. Nevertheless the dignity is a very high and rare one and was not conferred on any scientific man by the throne, from which<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I was graciously raised to it,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for more than 25 years.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The view from Mt Warning<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Northern NSW.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Michael Guilfoyle accompanied by William and two others climbed<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>it in April 1871, and described it in a letter to the local newspaper, quoted in Pescott (1974), pp. 52-3. Pescott gives William's membership of the party at p. 36.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>must be charming, and you with your poetic tendency &amp; ingenious spirit are sure to do justice to it.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me hope you are well and happy, &amp; that you will not miss your years of youth in building up a domestic home.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">With every sentiment of regard yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The difficulties in my department are not yet overcome. Do you think, that if I placed a few £ into your hands for red Cedar seeds, the sawyers would secure such through their children for me?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Chinese &amp; Assam Tea ought to grow famously in your place also<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Peru Bark</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>plants. All these I could send you, if you will indicate the way and require them.</p>
         </div>
